<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/celine-eu/v0.5> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://purl.org/peco/peco-core> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/w3c/sdw/dee1bdd3c339d8a0ab512c7f9bc97a08912ad7d6/ssn/integrated/sosa.ttl> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://saref.etsi.org/core/v3.1.1/saref.ttl> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#imports> <https://saref.etsi.org/saref4ener/v1.2.1/saref4ener.ttl> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/created> "2026-03-24"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The CELINE Core Ontology is a lightweight orchestration profile for\n    Renewable Energy Communities (RECs) and Digital Twin workflows. It connects established\n    standards — PECO, SAREF, SAREF4ENER, SOSA/SSN — without redefining their domain\n    semantics, providing a minimal coordination layer for simulation scenarios, dataset\n    references, KPI definition and evaluation, and REC flexibility commitment and settlement." .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-05-05"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "CELINE Core Ontology" .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespacePrefix> "celine" .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/preferredNamespaceUri> "https://w3id.org/celine-eu#" .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Version 0.5 introduces a generic, REC-centric KPI container (KPIDefinition,\n    KPICatalog, KPIScope, KPICalculationMethod, KPITemporalGranularity) and removes the direct\n    BIGG and BIGG4KPI imports. KPI alignment to external vocabularies (BIGG, SAREF, SAREF4ENER,\n    SOSA) is now expressed via SKOS mapping annotations on KPI classes rather than via OWL\n    imports. Existing KPIEvaluation usage is preserved with mandatory\n    linkage to a KPIDefinition." .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CELINE Core Ontology" .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://celine-eu.github.io/> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://github.com/celine-eu> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://www.celineproject.eu/> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#priorVersion> <https://w3id.org/celine-eu/v0.4> .
<https://w3id.org/celine-eu> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "0.5.0" .
